President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring September 15th as National POW/MIA Recognition Day in the United States. This day is dedicated to honoring American prisoners of war and service members who are missing in action. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of remembering the sacrifices made by these individuals and their families, as well as the ongoing mission to account for all missing personnel. The flag symbolizing America's Missing in Action and Prisoners of War will be flown at various locations across the country as a solemn reminder of this commitment. The proclamation calls upon the American people, as well as government officials and private organizations, to observe this day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.